<div class="dablink">This article is about the market trader.  For the racing driver, see <a href="/wiki/Nick_Leason" title="Nick Leason">Nick Leason</a>.</div>
<p><b>Nicholas "Nick" Leeson</b> (born 25 February 1967) is a former <a href="/wiki/Derivative_(finance)" title="Derivative (finance)">derivatives</a> <a href="/wiki/Trader_(finance)" title="Trader (finance)">trader</a> whose unsupervised and <a href="/wiki/Rogue_trader" title="Rogue trader">unauthorized speculative trading</a> on <a href="/wiki/Singapore" title="Singapore">Singapore</a>'s <a href="/wiki/Singapore_International_Monetary_Exchange" title="Singapore International Monetary Exchange">Singapore International Monetary Exchange</a> (SIMEX) caused the spectacular collapse of <a href="/wiki/Barings_Bank" title="Barings Bank">Barings Bank</a>, the <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a>'s oldest <a href="/wiki/Investment_bank" title="Investment bank" class="mw-redirect">investment bank</a>. He is currently the CEO of <a href="/wiki/Republic_of_Ireland" title="Republic of Ireland">Irish</a> <a href="/wiki/Football(soccer)" title="Football(soccer)" class="mw-redirect">football</a> club <a href="/wiki/Galway_United" title="Galway United" class="mw-redirect">Galway United</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
